  "prompt": "Clean Master, the Android app, deleted some of my important pictures when I tapped the \"clean the junk\" option. What are some methods to retrieve the pictures?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you lost your important pictures. Here are some methods to try to retrieve your deleted pictures:\n\n1. **Check the Recently Deleted Folder**:\n   Some Android devices have a \"Recently Deleted\" folder in the Gallery or Photos app where deleted files are temporarily stored for a period (typically around 30 days). Check this folder to see if your pictures are there.\n\n2. **Google Photos Backup**:\n   If you use Google Photos, your pictures might be backed up there. Open the Google Photos app and check if your pictures are available. If they were backed up before deletion, you should be able to restore them.\n\n3. **SD Card Recovery**:\n   If your pictures were stored on an SD card, you can remove the SD card from your phone and use a file recovery software on your computer to scan and recover deleted files. Examples of such software include Recuva, EaseUS Data Recovery Wizard, and Disk Drill.\n\n4. **Android Data Recovery Software**:\n   There are specialized Android data recovery applications that can help retrieve deleted files from your device's internal storage. Some popular choices include Dr.Fone, FoneLab, and Tenorshare UltData. You'll typically need to connect your phone to a computer and run the recovery software.\n\n5. **Cloud Services**:\n   If you use any cloud storage services like Dropbox, OneDrive, or Google Drive, your pictures might have been automatically backed up there. Check these services to see if your photos are available.\n\n6. **Contact App Support**:\n   Reach out to Clean Master's customer support. They might have specific steps or advice for recovering files that their app deleted.\n\n7. **Professional Data Recovery Services**:\n   If none of the above methods work, consider contacting professional data recovery services. These services can be costly but may offer the best chance of recovery if the data is crucial.\n\n**Important Note**: To improve the chances of recovery, try to limit the usage of your phone until you attempt recovery. Continuing to use the phone can overwrite the deleted data, making it harder to recover.\n\nI hope one of these methods helps you recover your pictures.",
